description._content: Description: Water-mills near Tembiun shewing the chutes above and the outlets. The entrance to the mill can be seen near the group of figures on the right. Location: Tembiun, Persia Description: The water-chutes and channels above the water-mills at Tembiun. Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
